📌 Tips for Text and Phrase Matching

Here are common matching patterns you can support:

User Wants	CQL Pattern

Exact phrase	text ~ "\"phrase here\""
Starts with	title ~ "plan*"
Contains keyword	text ~ "keyword"
Exclude term	text ~ "keyword" AND NOT text ~ "exclude"
Multiple keywords	(text ~ "a" AND text ~ "b")


To search for phrases containing spaces, wrap the phrase in double quotes and escape internal quotes as needed — e.g. text ~ "\"red line\"" for exact phrase matching. 


---

🛑 Limitations

✅ You can use CQL to filter by spaces, labels, type, text, title, creator, date, etc. 
❌ You cannot directly compare two fields in a CQL clause (e.g., no field-to-field comparisons). 
❌ You cannot make a space = ALL clause — just omit space if you want everything.


